[src:git/git-checkout] As a convenience, --track without -b implies branch creation.
[src:git/git-checkout] If no `-b` option is given, the name of the new branch will be derived from the remote-tracking branch, by looking at the local part of the refspec configured for the corresponding remote, and then stripping the initial part up to the "*".
[src:git/git-checkout] This would tell us to use `hack` as the local branch when branching off of `origin/hack` (or `remotes/origin/hack`, or even `refs/remotes/origin/hack`).
[src:git/git-checkout] If the given name has no slash, or the above guessing results in an empty name, the guessing is aborted.
[src:git/git-checkout] You can explicitly give a name with `-b` in such a case.
[src:git/git-checkout] Do not set up "upstream" configuration, even if the `branch.autoSetupMerge` configuration variable is true.
