[src:git/git-log-p02] For a complete list of ways to spell *<revision-range>*, see the *Specifying Ranges* section of gitrevisions[7].
[src:git/git-log-p02] Show only commits that are enough to explain how the files that match the specified paths came to be.
[src:git/git-log-p02] See *History Simplification* below for details and other simplification modes.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Paths may need to be prefixed with `--` to separate them from options or the revision range, when confusion arises.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Besides specifying a range of commits that should be listed using the special notations explained in the description, additional commit limiting may be applied.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Using more options generally further limits the output (e.g.
[src:git/git-log-p02] `--since=`*<date1>* limits to commits newer than *<date1>*, and using it with `--grep=`*<pattern>* further limits to commits whose log message has a line that matches *<pattern>*), unless otherwise noted.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Note that these are applied before commit ordering and formatting options, such as `--reverse`.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Limit the output to the first *<number>* commits that would be shown.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Limit the output to the last *<number>* commits that would be shown.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Skip *<number>* commits before starting to show the commit output.
[src:git/git-log-p02] As a special case, *today* means the last midnight.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Show all commits more recent than *<date>*.
[src:git/git-log-p02] This visits all commits in the range, rather than stopping at the first commit which is older than *<date>*.
[src:git/git-log-p02] Limit the commits output to ones with author/committer header lines that match the *<pattern>* regular expression.
